aa(lp73
VI started to think about what makes words real,
p74
aVbecause a lot of people ask me,
p75
aVthe most common thing I got from people is,
p76
aV"Well, are these words made up? I don't really understand."
p77
aVAnd I didn't really know what to tell them
p78
aVbecause once sonder started to take off,
p79
aVwho am I to say what words are real and what aren't.
p80
aVAnd so I sort of felt like Steve Jobs, who described his epiphany
p81
aVas when he realized that most of us, as we go through the day,
p82
aVwe just try to avoid bouncing against the walls too much
p83
aVand just sort of get on with things.
p84
aVBut once you realize that people \u2014
p85
aVthat this world was built by people no smarter than you,
p86
aVthen you can reach out and touch those walls
p87
aVand even put your hand through them
p88
aVand realize that you have the power to change it.
