aa(lp104
VBut then I decided, what people are really asking
p105
aVwhen they're asking if a word is real, they're really asking,
p106
aV"Well, how many brains will this give me access to?"
p107
aVBecause I think that's a lot of how we look at language.
p108
aVA word is essentially a key
p109
aVthat gets us into certain people's heads.
p110
aVAnd if it gets us into one brain,
p111
aVit's not really worth it,
p112
aVnot really worth knowing.
p113
aVTwo brains, eh, it depends on who it is.
p114
aVA million brains, OK, now we're talking.
p115
aVAnd so a real word is one that gets you access to as many brains as you can.
p116
aVThat's what makes it worth knowing.
