aa(lp140
VAnd I think, when we're all searching for meaning in our lives,
p141
aVand searching for the meaning of life,
p142
aVI think words have something to do with that.
p143
aVAnd I think if you're looking for the meaning of something,
p144
aVthe dictionary is a decent place to start.
p145
aVIt brings a sense of order
p146
aVto a very chaotic universe.
p147
aVOur view of things is so limited
p148
aVthat we have to come up with patterns and shorthands
p149
aVand try to figure out a way to interpret it
p150
aVand be able to get on with our day.
p151
aVWe need words to contain us, to define ourselves.
p152
aa(lp153
VI think a lot of us feel boxed in
p154
aVby how we use these words.
p155
aVWe forget that words are made up.
p156
aVIt's not just my words. All words are made up,
p157
aVbut not all of them mean something.
p158
aVWe're all just sort of trapped in our own lexicons
